  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for ffmpeg-7",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for ffmpeg-7 fixes the following issues\n\n- CVE-2026-40962: inadequate CENC subsample bounds checks can lead to an integer overflow (bsc#1262237).\n\nChanges for ffmpeg-7:\n\n- Update to version 7.1.4:\n * Codec, format, filter and various other bugfixes.\n * lavc/aarch64: Fix addp overflow in ff_pred16x16_plane_neon_10\n * swscale/output: Fix integer overflow in yuv2ya16_X_c_template()\n * avformat/avformat: clear FFFormatContext packet queue when\n closing a muxer\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
